subSubSection.paragraph:
The posterior end of the maxilla bifurcates into two processes (
Fig. 2A
), the lower of which underlies the jugal. The medial surface of this process extends higher than the lateral surface, and the jugal sits in a shallow trough between the two. The upper process is a vertical plate that separates two processes at the front of the jugal, the outer one of which covers the lateral surface of the maxilla. The medial edge of the distal end of the maxilla reaches the ectopterygoid (
Fig. 2B
), although there are no conspicuous contact surfaces on either bone.

